title: For Sale:  45 cal. ACP Ammo for Sale
postcontent: I have 650 rounds of freshly reloaded 45 cal. ACP.  These are loaded by me.  I have been reloading for 52 years now and continue to do so. I  only use the best materials in reloading. I only buy brass that is manufactured by, RP, WW, Starline, OFL, CBC, GFC, GFI, Federal, Speer, TZZ, PMC, S & B, Blazer.  This is Mixed Brass by these  Manufacturers. 99 % of this brass is  brass colored, you might find 6-8 silver casings.    I reload on a Dillon 5 station Progressive loader.  Here  is the goods.  Brass is tumbled for 6-8 hours using Walnut media. Then tumbled to remove Walnut media.   Each brass is then inspected for any cracks and any Walnut particles in brass.   Brass goes into reloader, deprimed, new cci primer installed, 5.6 grains of WINCHESTER   231 smokeless powder loaded, casing is sized, 230 grain MONTANA  Gold FMJ bullet installed and seated.  Round is sized to .452.  This is a standard average load in all the top reloading data manuals.  I do NOT load  HOT  Loads.  No need to.I shoot a couple hundred rounds a month myself.  I shoot a Springfield 45 cal. XDS,  and these rounds shoot  perfect, I have  NEVER had  a  NO-Fire or jam and thats  in  approx. 5000 rounds.This ammo comes in 50 round plastic boxes and paper boxes.  9 of the boxes  are plastic boxes from Berrys.  If you want the boxes great, I will have to charge you $2.00/box for the Berrys boxes and $1.00/box for the paper boxes with plastic trays.    I am selling this ammo at what it cost me to reload which is half price over store bought ammo..Store bought ammo is usually .40 to .44 cents/round.  My ammo is .21 cents  per round.  For 650 rounds the ammo will cost you $136.50.  The boxes will cost you $18.00 for the 9 Berrys boxes and $4.00 for the 4 paper boxes with plastic trays, for a GRAND TOTAL of  $158.50.If you do NOT want the ammo boxes,  your cost is  $136.50.  As a  protection for myself, Buyer will have to sign a Injury Waiver.

postcontent: Finally available for public consumption is the much anticipated Scorpion sub-gun. Imported as a pistol, it is a blowback-operated semi-auto in 9mm with a short 7¾” barrel. Equipped with our newly designed low-profile sights, its rear sight has four different aperture sizes for everything from close quarters to way out there. The sights ride on an 11” Picatinny rail perfect for mounting optics. 2016 models now feature 1/2×28 threads hidden underneath the factory flash-hider, meaning users can fit either 1/2×28 or 18×1 accessories to the muzzle. Also added is a QD sling swivel pocket integrated into the rear sling attachment point. Simple and reliable, the Scorpion not only has ambidextrous controls, its non-reciprocating charging handle is swappable and reach to the trigger is adjustable. Our favorite accessory for the Scorpion pistol is our new arm brace adapter, which quickly and easily adds an AR-style pistol buffer tube to the rear of the action, enabling the use of an arm brace for added stability. The CZ Scorpion EVO 3 S1 Pistol is legally classified by the ATF as a pistol, and is intended by CZ-USA to be used as a pistol. Under current federal law and ATF policy attaching a stock to this pistol – or attaching a device which is then used as a stock or intended to be used as a stock – constitutes the making of a short-barreled rifle which requires registration with ATF and the payment of the applicable tax. Users of the CZ Scorpion EVO 3 S1 Pistol bear the sole responsibility for ensuring their use of the firearm complies with all local, state, and federal firearms laws.

title: For Sale:  NiB CZ P07 9mm
postcontent: Introduced in 2009, the CZ P-07 was the first handgun to feature the convertible Omega trigger system. A simplification of the CZ 75’s hammer ignition method, the Omega’s trigger parts are interlocking in nature, allowing full disassembly and reassembly without the need for gunsmithing experience or tools. The best part of this system is its convertible decocker/safety system. Whether the user wants to carry the pistol cocked and locked like a 1911 or decocked for a double-action first pull of the trigger, a few minutes time allows the swapping of the safety for a decocking lever or vice versa. The P-07 received a facelift in 2014, removing any sharp edges and adding forward cocking serrations and interchangeable backstraps. Metal sights, new trigger and hammer designs and a fiber-reinforced polymer rounded out the updates, resulting in a pistol that’s even more comfortable for all-day carry, increasingly adaptable to user preferences and hardier than ever before.
